6:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Devin and GitHub Copilot share a solid foundation of core features including Code Generation, Code Review, Debugging, Refactoring. On the other hand, GitHub Copilot uniquely offers Autocomplete and Ide Integration, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Devin holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 6/10, while GitHub Copilot scores 9/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, GitHub Copilot comes in at a lower starting price of $10/mo, while Devin begins at $500/mo. Neither platform offers a free plan, so you will need to budget for at least the starting tier from the beginning. Be sure to take advantage of any trial periods they may offer."}]]}]
